  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="3"/>
   <head>
      <hi>A SONNET</hi> to the Christian Reader.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>
         <hi>
            <seg rend="decorInit">A</seg>
         </hi> Chilles neuer durst at once,</l>
      <l>with monsters two to fight,</l>
      <l>And yet at once this book shewes thee</l>
      <l>How three to put to flight.</l>
      <l>The Deuil, the World, the Flesh; and more,</l>
      <l>To conquer Death and sinne:</l>
      <l>And how to liue, and how to die,</l>
      <l>And how the heauens to winne.</l>
      <l>It is a path to Paradise,</l>
      <l>Aport to heauenlie blisse,</l>
      <l>It treats of truce, and bringes the peace,</l>
      <l>That euer during is.</l>
      <l>Then read, and reape the fruits thereof,</l>
      <l>And thanke thou for thy gaines</l>
      <l>The God aboue, who raisd vp those,</l>
      <l>That tooke for thee the paines.</l>
   </lg>
   <epigraph>
      <q>Conuertantur qui oderunt Sion.</q>
   </epigraph>
</div>
